{
  "bookId": "laozi-boshu",
  "num": 27,
  "title": "第二十七章（曳明）",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "善行者无轍迹 善言者无瑕適 善數者不用檮策 善閉者无關籥而不可啟也 善結者无纆約而不可解也"
    },
    {
      "text": "是以聖人恆善救人 而无棄人 物无棄財 是謂曳明"
    },
    {
      "text": "故善人 善人之師 不善人 善人之齎也"
    },
    {
      "text": "不貴亓師 不愛亓齎 唯知乎大眯 是謂眇要"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "heshanggong": [
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 45
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "善行道者求之於身，不下堂，不出門，故無轍跡。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 45
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "善言謂擇言而出之，則無瑕疵讁過於天下。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 45
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "善以道計事者，則守一不移，所計不多，則不用籌策而可知也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 45
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "善以道閉情欲、守精神者，不如門戶有關楗可得開。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 45
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "善以道結事者，乃可結其心，不如繩索可得解也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 1
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "聖人所以常教人忠孝者，欲以救人性命。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 23
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "使貴賤各得其所也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 23
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "聖人所以常教民順四時者，欲以救萬物之殘傷。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-9",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 23
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "聖人不賤名而貴玉視之如一。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-10",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 23
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "聖人善救人物，是謂襲明大道。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-11",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 23
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "人之行善者，聖人即以為人師。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-12",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 18
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "資，用也。人行不善者，聖人猶教導使為善，得以給用也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-13",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 1
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "獨無輔也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-14",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 20
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "無所使也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-15",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 20
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "雖自以為智。言此人乃大迷惑。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-16",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 20
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "能通此意，是謂知微妙要道也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ],
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 45
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "順自然而行，不造不始，故物得至而無轍迹也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 45
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "順物之性，不別不析，故無瑕讁可得其門也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 45
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "因物之數，不假形也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 45
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "因物自然，不設不施，故不用關楗繩約而不可開解也。此五者皆言不造不施，因物之性，不以形制物也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 45
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "聖人不立形名以檢於物，不造進向以殊棄不肖，輔萬物之自然而不為始，故曰無棄人也。不尚賢能，則民不爭，不貴難得之貨，則民不為盜，不見可欲，則民心不亂。常使民心無欲無惑，則無棄人矣。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 45
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "舉善以師不善，故謂之師矣。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 45
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "資，取也。善人以善齊不善，以善棄不善也。故不善人，善人之所取也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 45
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "雖有其智，自任其智，不因物，於其道必失。故曰，雖智大迷。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-9",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 45
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
